text.tspan: The ball must be hit over the net and land within the
boundaries of the court to be considered in play.
A player can hit the ball with their racket only once
before it crosses the net to their opponent's side.If a ball
hits the net and lands in the proper service area, the
serve is called a let, and the server gets another chance
Players are responsible for making calls on their own
side of the court. If there's a dispute, the players can ask
Tennis is played in sets, with each set being made up of games.
A game is won by being the first player to score four points and
have a lead of at least two points over the opponent.
